# EyeOn Platform Architecture

## You Are Here

Current workspace is **wp-eyeonportal-plugin** (WordPress). Ongoing
first-class public platform for centers on WordPress; consumes
web-app-backend via API token.

The EyeOn portal product spans multiple sibling applications. Always reason
about a change with these boundaries in mind and implement end-to-end across
all affected repos in a single session using the absolute paths below.

## Cross-Repo Edit Protocol

When implementing a feature in this session:

1. Identify all affected sibling repos from the table below.
2. Make changes directly in each repo using absolute paths — do not stop at
   the current workspace.
3. Schema/migrations: only in `admin-portal-backend/db/migrations/`.
4. Admin UI + staff flows: `admin-portal` + `admin-portal-backend`.
5. Public/read surface: `web-app-backend` (+ `center-website-runtime`, WP
   plugin, or kiosk when applicable).
6. Center website builder/runtime: `center-website` + `admin-portal-backend` +
   `web-app-backend`.
7. Never add business logic to public frontends; keep writes in
   `admin-portal-backend`.
8. Never invent APIs — locate or add endpoints in the correct backend first.

## Product Roles

| Role | App | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Entry | `admin-portal` | Staff dashboard; "Manage Website" magic link into builder |
| Admin API | `admin-portal-backend` | Protected REST API; owns Postgres schema |
| Public API | `web-app-backend` | Read-only API for public consumers (API token) |
| Builder | `center-website` | Author pages, sections, menus, domains, preview |
| Runtime | `center-website-runtime` | Serve published/test domains via `web-app-backend` |
| WordPress | `wp-eyeonportal-plugin` | WordPress/Elementor public sites (ongoing platform) |
| Kiosk | `kiosk-electron` | Touch kiosk + media-display (ads) for centers |

## Public Website Platforms (coexistence)

Centers may use **either or both** public website stacks long term:

| Platform | Stack | Status |
|---|---|---|
| WordPress + plugin | `wp-eyeonportal-plugin` | **Ongoing** — many clients keep WordPress for non-EyeOn site features |
| Center website | `center-website` + `center-website-runtime` | **Growing** — new and migrating centers; staging today |

- Both platforms consume the same center data via `web-app-backend` (API token).
- **Do not assume** all centers move to center-website. Full migration may
  happen over 2–3 years but is **not guaranteed**.
- Public API or data-shape changes must consider **both** WordPress plugin and
  center-website-runtime consumers unless explicitly scoped to one platform.

